%N A396823 Decimal expansion of the unique real solution to the equation (1 + erf(x/sqrt(2)))/2 = x.
%C A396823 (1 + erf(x/sqrt(2)))/2 is the cumulative distribution function of the standard normal distribution with mean 0 and standard deviation 1.
%H A396823 Nick Lord, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3618701">83.13 An Unusual Iteration Example</a>, The Mathematical Gazette, Vol. 83, No. 496 (1999), pp. 118-119.
%H A396823 Mathematics Stackexchange, <a href="https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1753506/how-to-find-the-intersection-of-the-normal-cdf-and-the-y-x-line">How to find the intersection of the normal CDF and the 'y = x' line?</a>, 2016.
%H A396823 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal_distribution">Normal distribution</a>.
%e A396823 0.783263929995929012648770847268103403231048133095485...
%t A396823 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[(1 + Erf[x/Sqrt[2]])/2 == x, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A396823 (PARI) solve(x = 1/2, 1, (2 - erfc(x/sqrt(2)))/2 - x)
